HAWKINS v. WARDEN OF THE MARYLAND PENITENTIARY [App. No. 100,

September Term, 1963.]

Decided January 29, 1964.

Before Henderson, Hammond, Prescott, Horney and Marbury, JJ.

PER Curiam.

For reasons stated in the opinion of Judge Prendergast below, the application for leave to appeal is hereby denied.

Application denied.
